Finding fixed:
- Structural boundary leak: refit_sglang_mx_runtime.py initially imported
  shared runtime helper behavior from refit_vllm_mx_runtime.py. That made the
  SGLang runtime proof depend on a vLLM-owned module and left the SGLang plan
  source label as a local override of a vLLM helper.
- Fix: extracted the shared pure helper layer into
  refit_mx_runtime_common.py. vLLM and SGLang now keep thin runtime-specific
  wrappers that set their own mode/plan_source labels while reusing the same
  endpoint-to-segment planning implementation. This removes the vLLM/SGLang
  ownership leak and reduced refit_vllm_mx_runtime.py from 823 to 733 lines.

Post-fix review result:
- No remaining cursor-code-review blockers found in the scoped diff.
- The SGLang role-split module is still a POC harness, but the heavy runtime
  orchestration remains runtime-specific and the shared helper is limited to
  pure metadata/parsing/planning logic.
- Documentation keeps same-node, cross-node, one-pod-per-rank, and production
  claims separated. It does not claim direct NIXL landing, full-model refit, or
  real RL trainer-loop integration.

